AN ACT
To repeal section 160.425, RSMo, and to enact in lieu thereof one new section relating to the
Missouri charter public school commission.
Be it enacted by the General Assembly of the State of Missouri, as follows:
1 Section A. Section 160.425, RSMo, is repealed and one new
2 section enacted in lieu thereof, to be known as section 160.425,
3 to read as follows:
1 160.425. 1. The "Missouri Charter Public School
2 Commission" is hereby created within the department of
3 elementary and secondary education with the authority to
4 sponsor high quality charter schools throughout the state of
5 Missouri.
6 2. The commission shall consist of nine members
7 appointed by the [governor, by and with the advice and
8 consent of the senate] state board of education. No more
9 than five of the members shall be of the same political
10 party. No more than two members shall be from the same
11 congressional district. The term of office of each member
12 shall be four years, except those of the members first
13 appointed, of which three shall be appointed for a term of
14 one year, two for a term of two years, two for a term of
15 three years, and two for a term of four years. At the
16 expiration of the term of each member, the [governor, by and
